# Prettier formatting

Authored content in this repo is formatted by Prettier 3 (config in
`.prettierrc.json`). The pre-commit hook will auto-format staged files of
these types and then run `prettier --check` — write code that's already
Prettier-clean so the hook stays a no-op.

## Scope of this rule

This rule covers files Prettier owns: Markdown, SCSS/CSS, JS/TS, JSON, and
data YAML under `_data/`. It does NOT cover Liquid HTML in `_layouts/` or
`_includes/`, or `_config.yml` — those are intentionally excluded in
`.prettierignore`. See `.cursor/rules/commit-hook.mdc` for hook mechanics.

## Defaults (do not contradict)

- 2-space indent, no tabs
- LF line endings, single trailing newline at EOF
- `printWidth`: 100, except Markdown which is 80
- Double quotes; trailing commas where ES5 allows
- Markdown `proseWrap: preserve` — never auto-rewrap prose paragraphs

## Do

- Let the formatter own whitespace; don't hand-tune indentation.
- Wrap long Markdown links/code at natural boundaries only.
- For SCSS, prefer one selector per line and `// line comments`.

## Don't

- Don't sprinkle `// prettier-ignore` or `<!-- prettier-ignore -->` without a
  concrete reason (e.g. an aligned table that Prettier mangles).
- Don't reformat files outside this rule's globs — Liquid HTML and `_config.yml`
  must keep their hand-authored layout.
